      • words

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> words()
        Obtains immutable list of words used in the name of the field.

        A word is a part of the name, the first letter of which should be capitalized when converting to CamelCase.

        So, the name is split by:

        • an underscore excluding it from a word;
        • a digit leaving it in a word.

        The name is split in such a manner, because the Protobuf compiler does in the same manner during the conversion to CamelCase.

        Specified by:
        words in interface UnderscoredName
        See Also:
        Protoc Camel Case
